I have made this soup twice. First time to the recipe and second I added grated turnip and I used fres nutmeg, hot paprika, and a pinch of cardamom. Took it to a party and it was a sure fire it!

Rating: 1
This made a thick and creamy soup, but the mace is overpowering, and the cabbage flavor is so subtle it fails to satisfy. The chives and parsley are absolutely necessary to offset the blandness and the mace. I loved the idea, but I won't be making this particular recipe again.

